org.jgentleframework.core.reflection
Interface MethodIdentification

All Superinterfaces:
Identification<java.lang.reflect.Method>, MemberIdentification<java.lang.reflect.Method>
public interface MethodIdentification
extends MemberIdentification<java.lang.reflect.Method>

This interface represents the method identification, designates a method or a set of methods corresponding to declaring class and one regular expression of name. The identification data shall be used conjointly with reflection tools in order to access specified methods.

setName

void setName(java.lang.String name)
Description copied from interface: Identification
Sets the name. You can use regular expression to specify a set of names.

EX:

setName("str*") will specify all of identification instance have "str" prefix.

Note: As concerns using SingleClassIdentification (an extension of Identification), the regular espression is not supported and the returned data array of Identification.getMember() method always has one element.

Specified by:
